%spark2.pyspark

sql="""
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS tbl_measurement (
     timestampdate      timestamp      COMMENT 'date'
   , location           STRING         COMMENT 'location'
   , parameter          STRING         COMMENT 'parameter'
   , interval           STRING         COMMENT 'interval'
   , measuring_unit     STRING         COMMENT 'measuring_unit'
   , value              INT            COMMENT 'value'
   , status             STRING         COMMENT 'status'
  )
  USING CSV 
  COMMENT '	https://opendata.swiss/de/dataset/stundlich-aktualisierte-luftqualitatsmessungen-seit-1983'
  
"""
spark.sql(sql)


sql="""
show tables
"""
spark.sql(sql).show()

%spark2.pyspark
#Daten werden eingelesen
print("Schema definiert" )

import os

from pyspark.sql.types import *

schema = [
    StructField("timestampdate",               TimestampType(), False),
    StructField("location",                    StringType(),  False),
    StructField("parameter",                   StringType(),  True),
    StructField("interval",                    StringType(),  True),
    StructField("measuring_unit",              StringType(),  True),
    StructField("value",                       FloatType(),  True),
    StructField("status",                      StringType(),  True),
  ]

df_measurement_data = spark.read.csv('all_pollution_data.csv',schema=StructType(fields=schema), header=True, timestampFormat = "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm", sep=',')
